        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> AFAIR from discussions in Ghostty, there's a huge performance difference between `ReleaseSafe` and `ReleaseFast`, where you absolutely want to use the latter for end-user builds. (`ReleaseSafe` is basically Zig's \"we have ASAN at home\".)\r\n\r\nEnd-user builds would have an explicit `-Doptimize=Release...`, in which case libuv would be built using that optimize mode.\r\n\r\n| -Doptimize      | libuv optimize |\r\n| --------------- | -------------- |\r\n| omitted (Debug) | ReleaseSafe    |\r\n| Debug           | ReleaseSafe    |\r\n| ReleaseSafe     | ReleaseSafe    |\r\n| ReleaseSmall    | ReleaseSmall   |\r\n| ReleaseFast     | ReleaseFast    |",
            "created_at": "2026-04-02T17:03:41Z",
